## Project Overview

**Project:** Athena v2 Services
**Architecture:** Layered Go API (cmd -> api/handlers -> services -> storage/repository -> PostgreSQL) + Java MPXJ microservice
**Tech Stack:** Go 1.25 (chi, GORM, JWT/SAML, OTEL), Java 17 (Spring Boot), Docker Compose, PostgreSQL, Azure Blob

## How to Build / Test / Run

**Validation command:** `make ci-checks` — runs format, vet, lint, mod tidy, vulncheck, and tests. Hard gate for all workflow commands.
For all build/test/run commands, see `agent_docs/build-and-test.md`.

## Issue Scopes

Scopes for commit messages and issue titles:
- `api`: HTTP handlers, routing, middleware (`internal/api/`)
- `storage`: Repository pattern, database queries (`internal/storage/`)
- `auth`: JWT, SAML, authentication/authorization (`internal/auth/`)
- `mpxj`: Java MPXJ microservice (`mpxj-service/`)

## Architecture Rules

- Handlers call services, services call repositories. No layer skipping.
- All database access through repository interfaces.
- MPXJ service accessed only through HTTP client (`internal/mpxj/`), never direct import.
- Swagger generation required after handler annotation changes: `make swag`.
